      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "NodeContract",
        "body": "Define the normative law for what every Twilite node schema must declare, what semantic meaning remains invariant, how the shared behavioral substrate is separated from optional composition, how declaration and connected fragments form one on-disk artifact, when that artifact is single-file versus multi-file, how a file explicitly declares itself as a fragment through a type node of type `fragment`, how a non-`fragment` node may serve as the root, how a runtime-generated root may discover sibling `.node` files without converting them into declared fragments, what payload and port shape is allowed, what mutations are permitted, and what validators must enforce before rendering or mutation proceeds. This contract does not assume every node is a content host or that one visual shell defines nodehood.",
        "category": "contracts",
        "authority": "normative",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "skill",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/skill-contract/skill.node-class.node",
