      "data": {
        "title": "Where This Applies",
        "body": "Use this contract whenever a Twilite node schema is defined or a Twilite node is created, mutated, rendered, loaded from disk, or validated. Every schema must declare type name, schema version, status, semantic meaning, required fields, allowed payload shape, fragment adjacency law, that fragment status is explicitly declared by a type node of type `fragment`, how runtime root discovery differs from declared fragments, whether the artifact is single-file or multi-file under that law, and any applicable root-only port law. The contract should also make clear which capabilities belong to the shared substrate and which are optional composition such as content, controls, ports, or special behaviors.",
        "conditions": [
          "A node is being created or updated.",
          "A node type schema is being defined.",
          "Validation needs to block invalid node structure.",
          "Rendering depends on a node resolving at least one view.",
          "Mutation policy must distinguish allowed updates from forbidden rewrites.",
          "Fragment connectivity or root-only port exposure must be enforced."
        ],
