      "data": {
        "title": "No Inferred Or Undocumented Structure",
        "body": "Editors, agents, and tools must not invent fields, infer missing schema, or silently guess structure for a node. Every required part must be declared by contract: metadata, semantic meaning, required fields, payload shape, root.node plus connected-fragment topology, explicit fragment declaration, whether the node is single-file or multi-file under that topology, root-only port exposure, and view resolution. The one exception is runtime root discovery, which may project sibling `.node` files through a generated root without reclassifying them as declared fragments. Undocumented keys are forbidden.",
        "severity": "high",
